ðŸ“Œ 1. Project Setup
Install (with npm or pnpm)
npm create vite@latest solana-dacit-ui --template react-ts
cd solana-dacit-ui

npm install @solana/web3.js @solana/wallet-adapter-base @solana/wallet-adapter-react @solana/wallet-adapter-react-ui @solana/wallet-adapter-wallets @coral-xyz/anchor


Also install some UI dependencies:

npm install @solana/wallet-adapter-react-ui @solana/wallet-adapter-phantom

ðŸ“Œ 2. Create Wallet Provider

This will let users connect wallets like Phantom.

src/WalletProvider.tsx
import React, { FC, ReactNode, useMemo } from "react";
import {
    ConnectionProvider,
    WalletProvider,
} from "@solana/wallet-adapter-react";
import { WalletAdapterNetwork } from "@solana/wallet-adapter-base";
import {
    PhantomWalletAdapter,
    SolflareWalletAdapter,
} from "@solana/wallet-adapter-wallets";
import { WalletModalProvider } from "@solana/wallet-adapter-react-ui";

import "@solana/wallet-adapter-react-ui/styles.css";

export const SolanaWalletProvider: FC<{ children: ReactNode }> = ({
    children,
}) => {
    const network = WalletAdapterNetwork.Devnet;

    const endpoint = useMemo(() => "https://api.devnet.solana.com", []);

    const wallets = useMemo(
        () => [new PhantomWalletAdapter(), new SolflareWalletAdapter()],
        []
    );

    return (
        <ConnectionProvider endpoint={endpoint}>
            <WalletProvider wallets={wallets}>
                <WalletModalProvider>{children}</WalletModalProvider>
            </WalletProvider>
        </ConnectionProvider>
    );
};

ðŸ“Œ 3. Load Anchor Program & IDL

Create a utility to load your Anchor Program using your deployed programâ€™s IDL.

src/utils/anchor.ts
import * as anchor from "@coral-xyz/anchor";
import idl from "./idl/dacit_program.json"; // copy your IDL here

const programID = new anchor.web3.PublicKey(idl.metadata.address);

export const getProvider = (wallet: any) => {
    const connection = new anchor.web3.Connection(
        "https://api.devnet.solana.com",
        "confirmed"
    );
    const provider = new anchor.AnchorProvider(connection, wallet, {});
    anchor.setProvider(provider);
    return provider;
};

export const getProgram = (wallet: any) => {
    const provider = getProvider(wallet);
    return new anchor.Program(idl as any, programID, provider);
};

ðŸ“Œ 4. Main App Component

This UI shows:

âœ” Wallet connect
âœ” Stake tokens
âœ” Unstake and claim rewards

src/App.tsx
import React, { useCallback, useState } from "react";
import { useAnchorWallet, useConnection, useWallet } from "@solana/wallet-adapter-react";
import { PublicKey } from "@solana/web3.js";
import { getProgram } from "./utils/anchor";

import "./App.css";

function App() {
    const { connection } = useConnection();
    const wallet = useAnchorWallet();

    const [stakeAmount, setStakeAmount] = useState<number>(0);

    const handleStake = useCallback(async () => {
        if (!wallet) return alert("Connect wallet first!");
        const program = getProgram(wallet);

        try {
            const tx = await program.methods
                .stakeTokens(new anchor.BN(stakeAmount))
                .accounts({
                    // ensure your accounts match your Anchor program
                    stakeState: new PublicKey(/* PDA addr */),
                    user: wallet.publicKey,
                    userAta: /* user's SPL token ATA */,
                    stakeVault: /* programâ€™s vault */,
                    mint: /* your DACIT mint */,
                })
                .rpc();
            console.log("Stake TX:", tx);
        } catch (err) {
            console.error("Stake failed:", err);
        }
    }, [wallet, stakeAmount]);

    const handleUnstake = useCallback(async () => {
        if (!wallet) return alert("Connect wallet first!");
        const program = getProgram(wallet);

        try {
            const tx = await program.methods
                .unstakeTokens()
                .accounts({
                    stakeState: new PublicKey(/* PDA addr */),
                    user: wallet.publicKey,
                    stakeVault: /* programâ€™s vault */,
                    userAta: /* userâ€™s ATA */,
                    mint: /* your DACIT mint */,
                })
                .rpc();
            console.log("Unstake TX:", tx);
        } catch (err) {
            console.error("Unstake failed:", err);
        }
    }, [wallet]);

    return (
        <div className="App">
            <h1>ðŸš€ DACIT Frontend</h1>
            {!wallet ? (
                <p>Connect your wallet to participate</p>
            ) : (
                <>
                    <div>
                        <input
                            type="number"
                            value={stakeAmount}
                            onChange={(e) => setStakeAmount(Number(e.target.value))}
                            placeholder="Amount to stake"
                        />
                        <button onClick={handleStake}>Stake Tokens</button>
                    </div>
                    <button onClick={handleUnstake}>Unstake & Claim Rewards</button>
                </>
            )}
        </div>
    );
}

export default App;

ðŸ“Œ 5. Wrap with Wallet Provider

Edit src/main.tsx:

import React from "react";
import ReactDOM from "react-dom/client";
import App from "./App";
import { SolanaWalletProvider } from "./WalletProvider";

ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById("root")!).render(
    <SolanaWalletProvider>
        <App />
    </SolanaWalletProvider>
);

âš¡ Key Concepts & Integration Tips
ðŸ’¡ Anchor Client via IDL

Anchor auto-generates an IDL (JSON) for your program at build time.

The client uses Program.methods.<instruction>() to construct transactions automatically, based on your programâ€™s IDL. 
Anchor Lang

ðŸ”‘ Wallet Integration

Use @solana/wallet-adapter-react to handle wallet connections smoothly.

Phantom and other wallets are supported.

Keep the Anchor provider linked to the wallet instance for signing transactions. 
Anchor Lang

ðŸ“Š Handling SPL Tokens

Before calling stake/unstake, you must ensure:

The user has an associated token account (ATA) for your token.

The programâ€™s vault ATA exists and is owned/controlled properly.

You can use @solana/web3.js or @solana/spl-token helpers to manage token accounts (create, fetch, balance query). 
Quicknode

